Paper: hep-th/0210095

Date: 2002-10-10

Title: Yang-Baxter $\sigma$-models and dS/AdS T-duality

Comments: 28 pages, LaTeX

Journal-ref: JHEP 0212 (2002) 051

We point out the existence of nonlinear $\sigma$-models on group manifoldswhich are left symmetric and right Poisson-Lie symmetric. We discuss thethe anisotropic principal chiral model and the $SL(2,C)/SU(2)$ WZW model. Thelatter has the de Sitter space as its (conformal) non-Abelian dual.